<p>Baltimore's Cold-Mixed climate presents unique opportunities for homeowners looking to invest in solar panels and upgrade their HVAC systems. With over 585,000 residents experiencing hot, humid summers and cold winters, the city's energy demands fluctuate significantly throughout the year. Baltimore receives approximately 213 sunny days annually, providing substantial solar generation potential despite the varied seasonal conditions. The combination of moderate solar irradiance and BGE's electricity rates of 13.5¬¢/kWh creates favorable conditions for solar investment returns.</p>

<p>BGE (Baltimore Gas and Electric) serves the Baltimore area with relatively stable utility rates, making solar panel installations increasingly attractive as energy costs continue to rise. The city's average home size of 1,620 square feet requires strategic HVAC planning to handle both summer cooling loads and winter heating demands efficiently. Baltimore's location in Maryland also provides access to excellent state-level solar incentives and net metering policies, while the federal tax credit further enhances the financial benefits of solar adoption for residents throughout Baltimore County.</p>

